<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About Us</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/main.css"> <!-- Link to your CSS file -->
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
            color: #333;
        }
        header {
            background: #333;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 1rem;
            text-align: center;
        }
        nav a {
            color: #fff;
            text-decoration: none;
            margin: 0 1rem;
        }
        .container {
            width: 80%;
            margin: auto;
            overflow: hidden;
            padding: 2rem;
        }
        .card {
            background: #fff;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            margin: 1rem 0;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }
        h2 {
            color: #333;
        }
        footer {
            background: #333;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 1rem;
            position: fixed;
            bottom: 0;
            width: 100%;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>About Us</h1>
        <nav>
            <a href="/">Home</a>
            <a href="/new-entry">New Entry</a>
            
        </nav>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
        <section class="card">
            <h2>Welcome to Your Book Management App!</h2>
            <p>Our application is designed to help you keep track of all the non-fiction books you read. With this app, you can:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Display a list of books you've read</li>
                <li>Sort books by title, date read, or rating</li>
                <li>Add new book entries with detailed information</li>
                <li>Update your reviews and notes</li>
                <li>Delete books and associated notes</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="card">
            <h2>Features</h2>
            <p>Our app provides a user-friendly interface with the following features:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Book Listing:</strong> View all books you have read in a sortable list.</li>
                <li><strong>Sorting:</strong> Easily sort books based on title, date, or rating.</li>
                <li><strong>Adding New Entries:</strong> Add new books with details like ISBN, title, author, and reviews.</li>
                <li><strong>Review Update:</strong> Edit your reviews for any book.</li>
                <li><strong>Book Deletion:</strong> Remove books and their notes from the system.</li>
                <li><strong>Notes:</strong> Add, update, and delete notes for each book.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="card">
            <h2>Technologies Used</h2>
            <p>This project leverages a variety of technologies to deliver a seamless experience:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Express.js:</strong> For server-side functionality.</li>
                <li><strong>EJS:</strong> For rendering dynamic HTML views.</li>
                <li><strong>PostgreSQL:</strong> For data storage and management.</li>
                <li><strong>Axios:</strong> For making HTTP requests to external APIs.</li>
                <li><strong>Node.js:</strong> For running the server-side code.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </div>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2024 Book Management App. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
